<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When the requested format is explicitly specified (and not a "fuzzy" format), then new Zend_Date() should throw an error when the input fails to match that format.</p>

<p>When a developer specifies a precise date $format for "new Zend_Date($date, $format)", an error should be thrown on invalid input.  Exceptions should be carefully noted in the documentation (e.g. Zend_Date::DATES).</p>

<p>For example, if a developer requests Zend_Date::DATE_MEDIUM date format, but the input does not match the format, then an error should be thrown.</p>

